    <summary>CLI-first remote terminal: manage many coding-agent/shell sessions and drive them from your phone.</summary>
    <description>
cordless is a **CLI-first remote terminal**. Install it on your dev box or laptop, run `cordless`, and
it opens a full-screen terminal dashboard with a **pairing QR** — scan it with the cordless phone app
and your sessions (shell, Claude Code, Codex, GitHub Copilot, or your own custom launchers) are in your
pocket.

### Highlights
- **Self-contained** — bundles its own Node runtime + `node-pty`; nothing else to install.
- **Persistent sessions** that survive disconnects and reboots, with scrollback **history**.
- **Chrome-style tab groups**, **custom launchers**, per-session **attention state** (know which agent is waiting for you), and phone notifications.
- **Open a session in a new terminal tab** (`o` in the dashboard) — like browser tabs.
- **Secure by default** — per-device hashed tokens, single-use pairing codes only the local daemon can mint, an Origin allowlist, and strict headers; never runs as root, never exposed to the internet (use Tailscale).

### After install
Run `cordless` to start the daemon and show the pairing QR. Optionally `cordless install` to start the daemon at login.

### Notes
This package downloads the official self-contained CLI zip from the project's GitHub release and verifies its SHA256 (see `tools\VERIFICATION.txt`). Licensed under **PolyForm Noncommercial 1.0.0** (free for noncommercial use; source-available).
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/naveenneog/cordless/releases/tag/v0.8.3</releaseNotes>
